    <briefdescription>
<para>RTC (Real-Time Clock) driver. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Thin wrapper over <ref refid="syn__port__rtc_8h" kindref="compound">syn_port_rtc.h</ref> that adds input validation and Unix-epoch conversion utilities. No heap allocation; no state struct is required — calls delegate directly to the port layer.</para>
<para>Epoch base: 1970-01-01 00:00:00 UTC (standard Unix time). Valid date range: 1970-01-01 through 2105-12-31.</para>
<para>Usage: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structSYN__RTC__DateTime" kindref="compound">SYN_RTC_DateTime</ref><sp/>dt<sp/>=<sp/>{<sp/>.<ref refid="structSYN__RTC__DateTime_1aa1d199dfe090313cbed0669888f96344" kindref="member">year</ref>=2025,<sp/>.month=6,<sp/>.day=1,</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.hour=12,<sp/>.minute=0,<sp/>.second=0<sp/>};</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__rtc_8c_1a67ae62050487193c6d607b4d427fa38f" kindref="member">syn_rtc_init</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__rtc_8c_1a5f25f12ab63bed6d1198f490c168941f" kindref="member">syn_rtc_set</ref>(&amp;dt);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>...<sp/>later<sp/>...</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__rtc_8c_1a926241f6738030cde97cf098e1a113a0" kindref="member">syn_rtc_get</ref>(&amp;dt);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">uint32_t<sp/>t<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="syn__rtc_8c_1a395c6dce5393ad644d2e2bd36a513779" kindref="member">syn_rtc_to_epoch</ref>(&amp;dt);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
